      • getIterationIndex

        public int getIterationIndex()
        Description copied from interface: TaskId
        When Control Flow actions are performed on Tasks, some tasks are replicated. A task replicated by a FlowActionType.IF action is differentiated from the original by an incremented Iteration Index. This index is reflected in the readable name of the Task's id (TaskId.getReadableName()), this methods safely extracts it and returns it as an int.
        Specified by:
        getIterationIndex in interface TaskId
        Returns:
        the iteration number of this task if it was replicated by a IF flow operation (>= 0)
        See Also:
        TaskId.getIterationIndex()

      • getReplicationIndex

        public int getReplicationIndex()
        Description copied from interface: TaskId
        When Control Flow actions are performed on Tasks, some tasks are replicated. A task replicated by a FlowActionType.REPLICATE action is differentiated from the original by an incremented Replication Index. This index is reflected in the readable name of the Task's id (TaskId.getReadableName()), this methods safely extracts it and returns it as an int.
        Specified by:
        getReplicationIndex in interface TaskId
        Returns:
        the iteration number of this task if it was replicated by a IF flow operation (>= 0)
